                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d969">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/9–1244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-12T23:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 12, 1944—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 13—10:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1718. In conversation with the Prime Minister<note n="92" xml:id="d969fn92">Sükrü
                        Saraçoğlu.</note> today I inquired as to whether his Government had now
                    prepared to sign the mutual aid agreement. Saraçoğlu replied that he was not
                    familiar with the present status of the matter but that he would look into it at
                    once and if as I assured him the text of the agreement had been virtually agreed
                    upon at the time Lend-Lease shipments were discontinued there should be no
                    difficulty in concluding the agreement in the near future. I told him that the
                    changes we desired in the text were not of great importance and expressed the
                    hope that he would direct the appropriate officials of the Foreign Office to
                    give the matter their immediate attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
